<div class="row" ng-controller="geoDataController">
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <h2>UNA</h2>
    <h3>Utility Network Audit</h3>
    <p>The Utility Network Audit is a review of installed infrastructure within Lagos State, ordered by LASIMRA, and performed by CIS under authority from LASIMRA.</p>
    <p>The current focus of UNA reflects the focus of LASIMRA, that is, telecommunications infrastructure. UNA will specifically be reviewing underground telecommunications infrastructure.</p>
    <p>GeoData is: <span class="text-muted">{{IsDbConnected ? "connected" : "not available"}}</span></p>
    <ul>
      <li ng-repeat="gd in geoData">{{Id}}</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <h2>LASIMRA</h2>
    <h3>Lagos State Infrastructure Maintenance and Regulatory Agency</h3>
    <p>
      LASIMRA is responsible for all infrastructure in public space.
    </p>
    <p>
      LASIMRA's responsibilities overlap with several other Lagos State agencies.
      In these cases LASIMRA's statutory responsibilities are to work with the other agencies in coordinating all activities related to the infrastructure.
    </p>
    <p>
      LASIMRA also has specific responsibilities with respect to managing telecommunications infrastructure. 
      The Utility Network Audit is just one example of LASIMRA performing its mandated duties.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <h2>CIS</h2>
    <h3>Critical Infrastructural Services Ltd.</h3>
    <p>
      CIS is a multinational business with its head office in Lagos.
    </p>
    <p>
      CIS specialises in auditing installed infrastructure, especially underground infrastructure.
    </p>
    <p>
      CIS has retained international expertise in underground drilling (no-dig), auditing of underground infrastructure, GIS systems development, general systems development, business analysis and policy development.  And is providing these services to LASIMRA.
    </p>
  </div>
